From 4b1beb57cba590412a6023c15bb30e26de9fabba Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vikram Kandukuri <vikram@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 23 Jul 2025 23:08:08 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] UPSTREAM:CP:ath12k: Add Enhanced Debug Information for
 Copy Engine Stats.

Enhance CE Pipe strcuture to include detailed debug information for
improved visibility and troubleshooting of CE (Copy Engine)
tasklet/work queue behavior, especially during target or host asserts.
Below support is added as part of this patch series

Tasklet/Work Queue Execution Time Bucketing:

 1. Group tasklets based on their execution time per CE into predefined
    time windows.
 2. Each group will include:
     Count of tasklets falling into that time window.
     Timestamp of the last update.

Tasklet/Work Queue Scheduled-to-Execution Time Bucketing:

 1. Group tasklets based on the time taken from scheduling to execution
    completion.
 2. Each group will include:
    Count of tasklets in that time window.
    Timestamp of the last update.

Recent Tasklet/Work Queue Timing  History:

 1. Maintain the last 20 records of tasklet execution and
    scheduled-to-execution times.
 2. The number of records is controlled via a macro, allowing future
    configurability.

These stats will be printed automatically during Target asserts and Host
asserts.
Added Minidump() support as well.

This will aid in diagnosing issues related to CE ring behavior.

Signed-off-by: Vikram Kandukuri <vikram@qti.qualcomm.com>
